<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/265: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-10T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">July 10,
                                            1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        July 11, 7.11 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your July 8th, 6 p.m. 1 and 2. Leguia planning elections extent of
                                which not yet known. Has promised last three days would publish
                                decree thereon. Promises press to publish tomorrow.</p>
                            <p>3. No tangible evidence now in possession of the Legation and none so
                                far obtainable. Having military attaché discreetly investigate.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>